attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB pie executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, for GNU/Linux 2.0.0, with debug_info, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a Linux variant of the Akira ransomware, written in Rust. It specifically targets VMware ESXi environments by enumerating and stopping virtual machines using the command `vmsvc/getallvms | ... | vim-cmd vmsvc/power.off`. The malware then encrypts files, focusing on virtual machine-related extensions like `.vmdk`, `.vmem`, and `.vmx` within `/vmfs/volumes` datastores. It uses a hardcoded public key and contains Tor onion IOCs such as `akiral2iz6a7qgd3ayp3l6yub7xx2uep76idk3u2kollpj.onion` for C2 or payment purposes.
